			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, I started playing EQ 3months after it came out. I have a Rogue on Drinal that is so good I have become bored with him. My cure? I have decided to start brand new on the newest server! Which class? Well, I have ALWAYS wanted to play a bard! I am presently 27th level, have the trubadors armor and long sword, 2 opalline earrings, and I went with full charisma and picked a human. I can pull pretty darn good, however, AE kiting is not working. My puter allows me to do 4 songs at once with ease, however, I seem to be having trouble in the kiting department. At an earlier level, I was able to kite Young Kodiaks pretty good using CoD, however, lately, I have tried Griffenes, and well, its not working. I use the best single target DD to pull(14pt dam), and then gather 3 or 4 of them. I switch to my horn and put up the AOE 20pt/tick DOT. I also put on my speed buff and switch back and forth. They whack me everytime I try and close the circle enough to get a hit with the dot. I can not seem to get it to work. Any advice for a Bard of 27, almost 28th level? Where to hunt? What to hunt? What song combo's to try? What items to try and get that I don't have? I would really appreshiate some advice here. I have refused hand-outs from in-game players as I want to make it on my own, however, there have been so many changes to the Bard class, I am kind of lost ATM. I need to be guided back onto the right path. Please help.</span></td>
