				<td colspan="2"><span>Nah, most people will not notice any fine subtleties like that.  (It's too bad they don't).  
<br />

<br />
What they generally CAN tell about a good Bard is a steady stream of nicely times single pulls, and/or doubles mezparked and ready to slaughter.  They might also cheer you a bit if you save them from a nasty pull with three or more adds.
<br />

<br />
