				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Advantages?<a name="55274"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 5 04 12:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I got out there to Dawnshroud and gave it a good try. I went near the shroom house. Before the house though, there were 3 shrooms ranging blue to yellow at 27th level. I am able to kite those very well, almost without a hitch. The problem comes as each one reaches 19% health, they begin to move in a straight line away from the kite circle. What I have found to work is that I continue circling until the 3rd one breaks off. However, as I kill the closest one to me, the last to break off, the first 2 continue moving. Now, DS is kinda dangerous. Lightcrawlers, blood starved wolves are right in that area. Several times as I killed 1 or 2, by the time i chased down the 3rd, it was in the area of the crawlers and often a wolf jumped me, forcing me to zone as they are red. I tried charming the shroom to fight the wolf, or another shroom, however, it too proved dangerous and difficult to manage. I found that doing 3 shrooms at a time works great in the end. There are 2 banks of 3 shrooms before the shroom house, then there are like 3, 3shroom areas inside the house. I did also go into the shroom house and pull all 9 or so shrooms at once at first. I pulled them all the way to where the 3 other shrooms were killed. This worked also to an extend, however, same problem, they began to move off one by one. It is difficult to circle in such a way to capture all mobs in the damage radius every tick, every single rotation. The mechanics to do so are just not there. I died doing the 9 at once in the end. Any ideas on what to try, or another, better, safer place to go? Getting the 3 at a time is decent xp, but now, almost all are blue to 28. If no better place presents itself, I will consider sticking it out til 29 or 30 there at the shrooms. I am starting the first of the Lambent quests at 30 also, the bracers. I went into Unrest for the greater dark bones that drop the darkbone bracelets but they were red to me. The griffenes in NK I can handle fine for their charms. Havent gotten one yet though. Thank you all for the great advice. Kiting is greatly dependent to the mobs. </span></td>
