				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Advantages?<a name="55447"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 6 04 11:54 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, I have given the Snow Cougars a shot in Iceclad. I like them much better then the shrooms in DS. 
<br />

<br />
Cons:
<br />
1) It is way out of the way. Any death involves either a port or a lengthy run, though bard speed helps alot and alleviates having to get a sow. 
<br />

<br />
2) Midnight is a pain in the a$. That black cat is a random spawn on either of the islands. The gnomes too can get close and if on the ToFS island, the shadow guardians also.
<br />

<br />
3) They are camped fairly consistently on the gnome island.
<br />

<br />
4) Loot is not the best.
<br />

<br />
Pros:
<br />
1) Plenty of cats to pull. If I use both dot songs and speed song I can circle them effectively.
<br />

<br />
2) These cats do not run off as they get low on hits. Only the last cat will stop and move away but by that time he is easy prey.
<br />

<br />
3) The xp is very sweet. At 27 I was able to even kill midnight with CoD so if you keep it to just cats, you will do fine.
<br />

<br />
Summary: Iceclad and SNow cougars are probably the best xp you will find for circle kiting. The xp is wonderful and you do get some plat for your efforts and a close by place to sell them and buy food and water. I recommend NOT doing more then 5 or 6 and this is because if you get hit, you definately feel it. One death is not worth it, you are better off just sticking to a nominal number of cats at one time. I tried up to 14, however, I found doing just 5 is much more consistent xp.
<br />

<br />
I know many of these points were already mentioned I just wanted to hit home how accurate and up to date they are. THank you all for your advice, it has worked for me well.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
